        <num>CC 2487</num>
        <heading>2487.  Delivery excused until payment of price and for insolvency</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 2487.  Delivery excused until payment of price and for insolvency
The seller may refuse to deliver the thing sold until the buyer tenders payment of the price, unless the seller has granted the buyer a term for such payment.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
